webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) "5 cairns in trees. Text on the back: “Howling monkey group. The perception of the howling monkey is the roofs for that of the jaguar. The throat is with a bony box that is believed to act as sounding board. The Text may be for two miles.”: Included in series with photons. 2941-2954. See also series with photon. 2930-2940 with postcards partly the same motif, non-coloured.' - https://www.europeana.eu/item/52/gnm_photo_GNM2934_001. Göteborgs naturhistoriska museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021015942704. CC BY - http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/2.5/
